The article is a statement from the President on the passage of financial reform. The President expresses his gratitude to Chairman Dodd and Chairman Frank for their efforts in passing the reform, which aims to protect consumers and prevent future financial crises. The reform includes strong consumer financial protections, greater transparency in financial transactions, and the implementation of the Volcker rule to protect Americans' savings. The President emphasizes the importance of a thriving financial sector operating within a framework of rules and regulations. He looks forward to the bill being passed in the Senate and signed into law.